INTAKE RUN SUMMARY
posting-title: Full-Stack Developer (Python/FastAPI + React) Compliance SaaS, Large-File Parsing & Rules Engine
client-domain: B2B SaaS - Compliance & Accounting Automation
posted: Yesterday
budget: EUR 4,000 (fixed-price, milestone-based across 6 milestones)

POSTING STRUCTURE
The client is well-organized and specific:
- Domain registered, company incorporated, architecture decided
- Consolidated technical specification + field-level parsing reference docs provided
- Interactive HTML design prototype as binding visual reference
- Not exploratory; looking for reliable mid-to-senior developer to build from scratch

CORE SCOPE (7 features)
1. Unified file-format detector: XML/PDF routing by document type, period, version
2. Streaming XML parsers: lxml/iterparse memory-stable up to 500+ MB; PDF embedded XML extraction
3. Asynchronous processing: Celery + Redis with separate heavy/light queues, job lifecycle
4. Business rules engine: 170+ documented reconciliation rules across document types, configurable thresholds, drill-down
5. Analytical dashboard: tables, charts, trend/anomaly analysis, server-side pagination (100k+ rows), Excel/PDF export
6. Multi-tenant architecture: full data isolation per client account, enforced at API level
7. Subscription billing: Stripe (trial, plans, proration, webhooks, cancellation)

TECH STACK (LOCKED)
Backend: Python (FastAPI)
Frontend: React + TypeScript
Database: PostgreSQL
Queue: Celery + Redis
Storage: AWS S3 or Azure Blob
Auth: Supabase or Auth0 (hard requirement - behind adapter module)
Payments: Stripe
Hosting: AWS or Azure
Client states: "Well-argued alternatives can be discussed at kickoff; the stack will not change mid-project."

DELIVERY METHODOLOGY
- 6 milestones with written DoD and acceptance criteria
- Automated tests required: golden-file suites against fixtures, min 70% coverage on business logic, zero critical static analysis findings
- Milestone 2 payment gate: live POC parsing 500+ MB XML via iterparse + memory profile before proceeding
- Weekly status (Mondays); demo call end of each milestone (pre-agreed script)
- EU timezone preferred
- All code in private GitHub repo owned by client

CLIENT SELECTION CRITERIA
Looking for:
1. Proven experience shipping SaaS web applications end-to-end
2. Demonstrable experience processing large structured files (size + approach required)
3. Familiarity with multi-tenant isolation and async job architectures
4. Clean code, honest communication, reliable delivery
5. Domain knowledge NOT required (documentation covers it)

SCREENING QUESTIONS (REQUIRED FOR PROPOSAL)
Q1: "What is the largest XML or structured file you have processed in production, and what was your approach to memory management?"
   -> Tests: real production experience, memory-aware architecture decisions

Q2: "How would you enforce tenant isolation in a FastAPI + PostgreSQL application, and at which layers?"
   -> Tests: multi-tenant architecture understanding, security-conscious design

CRITICAL NOTES
- Client may request paid probation task (parse real XML, return structured data via REST) before full build
- Not "figure it out as you go" - specification is consolidated, reference docs complete, visual design locked
- This is a serious, well-scoped engagement for a mid-to-senior developer
- Risk areas for proposal: must answer Q1 and Q2 concretely with production examples; must demonstrate large-file handling; must address tenant isolation layers explicitly

